brick /brɪk/

(bricks) 

1. N-VAR Bricks are rectangular blocks of baked clay used for building walls, which are usually red or brown. Brick is the material made up of these blocks. 砖 

例： She built bookshelves out of bricks and planks. 她用砖和厚木板制作了书架。 

2. PHRASE If you hit a brick wall or come up against a brick wall , you are unable to continue or make progress because something stops you. 碰壁 [非正式] 

例： After that my career just seemed to hit a brick wall. 从那以后我的事业似乎碰了壁。

